1
00:00:05,771 --> 00:00:07,471
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,541 --> 00:00:09,181
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,611 --> 00:00:12,041
(Episode 46)

4
00:00:16,551 --> 00:00:17,981
(Police Officer True To The Basics)

5
00:00:19,721 --> 00:00:20,721
Jo Mi Hyang.

6
00:00:41,811 --> 00:00:42,811
You're laughing?

7
00:00:43,241 --> 00:00:44,411
So nice to see you.

8
00:00:44,911 --> 00:00:46,751
I thought I'd never see you again.

9
00:00:47,681 --> 00:00:48,881
You're here for...

10
00:00:49,551 --> 00:00:51,421
an apology from me, right?

11
00:00:53,321 --> 00:00:55,121
You're not sorry at all, are you?

12
00:00:56,761 --> 00:00:58,461
I'm truly sorry.

13
00:00:58,961 --> 00:01:00,031
Ms. Na.

14
00:01:00,961 --> 00:01:02,231
I was wrong.

15
00:01:07,271 --> 00:01:08,401
Let me ask you one thing.

16
00:01:09,671 --> 00:01:11,341
Why did you keep coming
to the pharmacy?

17
00:01:12,141 --> 00:01:13,541
Were you trying to see
if I was looking...

18
00:01:14,071 --> 00:01:15,371
for the husband you hid?

19
00:01:15,641 --> 00:01:19,151
- Was that why you kept coming by?
- No, the truth is...

20
00:01:20,711 --> 00:01:23,151
I went to watch you, Ms. Na.

21
00:01:25,281 --> 00:01:26,291
What?

22
00:01:26,691 --> 00:01:28,821
To watch someone like you,
who has everything,

23
00:01:29,121 --> 00:01:31,221
lose her husband
and live like a widow.

24
00:01:32,361 --> 00:01:33,431
Just to watch.

25
00:01:35,291 --> 00:01:36,601
You crazy...

26
00:01:36,661 --> 00:01:39,301
What good were your fancy doctor son
and daughter-in-law?

27
00:01:41,671 --> 00:01:44,471
How miserable and unhappy
you must have been.

28
00:01:44,901 --> 00:01:45,971
Right?

29
00:01:52,981 --> 00:01:53,981
You're...

30
00:01:54,481 --> 00:01:55,481
laughing?

31
00:01:57,381 --> 00:01:58,381
In your eyes,

32
00:01:59,191 --> 00:02:00,451
did I seem unhappy to you?

33
00:02:00,721 --> 00:02:01,721
Of course.

34
00:02:02,261 --> 00:02:05,561
- Your husband was gone 30 years.
- No.

35
00:02:06,291 --> 00:02:07,561
I was happy.

36
00:02:08,591 --> 00:02:12,431
I earned the money myself.
I fed and raised my kids myself.

37
00:02:12,501 --> 00:02:15,371
I protected my family myself,
and I was truly happy.

38
00:02:15,501 --> 00:02:16,771
That's my life.

39
00:02:17,471 --> 00:02:20,241
The likes of you could never
make me unhappy.

40
00:02:20,541 --> 00:02:24,311
Don't lie.
You were living in nightmare.

41
00:02:24,681 --> 00:02:27,411
You lost 30 years because of me.

42
00:02:27,481 --> 00:02:30,381
No. The one who lost 30 years...

43
00:02:31,051 --> 00:02:32,051
was you.

44
00:02:33,391 --> 00:02:35,961
How unhappy you must have been,
living in hiding for 30 years.

45
00:02:36,391 --> 00:02:37,391
Killing your own brother,

46
00:02:37,461 --> 00:02:38,991
and stealing
another woman's husband.

47
00:02:39,691 --> 00:02:41,091
How scared you must have been...

48
00:02:41,131 --> 00:02:43,201
that Gong Gi Cheol
would regain his memory.

49
00:02:43,261 --> 00:02:44,261
How terrified were you...

50
00:02:44,331 --> 00:02:45,901
that you'd end up getting
caught like this?

51
00:02:46,371 --> 00:02:47,771
You didn't have a single day
of peace, did you?

52
00:02:48,071 --> 00:02:50,841
- Afraid that we would find you.
- Don't be so smug.

53
00:02:51,101 --> 00:02:54,511
- Hate me. Despise me.
- No.

54
00:02:54,811 --> 00:02:57,811
- I'm going to pity you.
- Don't you dare pity me.

55
00:02:58,311 --> 00:03:02,581
Live the rest of your life in agony,
tormented by betrayal.

56
00:03:02,681 --> 00:03:05,051
I'm going to forget you,
Jo Mi Hyang.

57
00:03:06,221 --> 00:03:09,321
And I'm going to live happily
for the rest of my life.

58
00:03:09,391 --> 00:03:10,521
So you...

59
00:03:12,361 --> 00:03:14,831
can spend the rest of your life
being miserable in prison.

60
00:03:19,201 --> 00:03:20,331
Hey!

61
00:03:21,601 --> 00:03:22,601
Let's go.

62
00:03:24,041 --> 00:03:25,241
Gong Gi Cheol...

63
00:03:26,571 --> 00:03:27,571
The one who started the rumor...

64
00:03:27,641 --> 00:03:29,311
that he was having an affair
with the herbal clinic woman.

65
00:03:29,841 --> 00:03:30,841
That was me.

66
00:03:34,251 --> 00:03:36,851
As it turned out,
the woman from the herbal clinic...

67
00:03:37,151 --> 00:03:38,851
left on the very same day.

68
00:03:39,291 --> 00:03:42,791
So I just made an offhand comment
to the neighbors,

69
00:03:43,191 --> 00:03:44,391
and what do you know,

70
00:03:44,991 --> 00:03:46,491
they all believed me.

71
00:03:47,831 --> 00:03:49,901
Because of me,

72
00:03:50,461 --> 00:03:52,401
30 years of your lives
went up in smoke.

73
00:03:53,201 --> 00:03:55,771
So? Still want to pity me?

74
00:03:56,401 --> 00:03:57,501
The rest of your life...

75
00:03:58,301 --> 00:04:00,271
Do you really think
you can live happily?

76
00:04:03,111 --> 00:04:06,951
- You evil witch. I'll kill you.
- Take her away.

77
00:04:07,011 --> 00:04:10,221
- I'll kill you. I'll kill you.
- Take her away.

78
00:04:10,381 --> 00:04:11,721
Hey!

79
00:04:11,781 --> 00:04:13,391
(Police Officer True To The Basics)

80
00:04:13,451 --> 00:04:14,691
You spent your lives being fooled,

81
00:04:14,751 --> 00:04:16,321
just believing
what people told you, right?

82
00:04:17,491 --> 00:04:21,291
You pathetic, naive fools.

83
00:04:23,431 --> 00:04:26,871
I'll kill you.
You, I'm going to kill you!

84
00:04:29,701 --> 00:04:32,971
How could you?
How could you do this?

85
00:04:33,041 --> 00:04:35,211
Are you even human?

86
00:04:45,851 --> 00:04:47,591
Mom.

87
00:05:06,071 --> 00:05:07,411
So everyone...

88
00:05:08,171 --> 00:05:11,411
thought I had an affair
with Seon Chul's wife...

89
00:05:12,141 --> 00:05:14,411
and that we ran away together
in the middle of the night.

90
00:05:15,821 --> 00:05:16,851
Yes.

91
00:05:18,581 --> 00:05:20,351
Then what about Seon Chul's wife?

92
00:05:21,291 --> 00:05:23,891
After she left home,
she stayed at a temple.

93
00:05:24,591 --> 00:05:27,131
She passed away not too long ago.

94
00:05:28,591 --> 00:05:32,131
And I had no idea
when I asked what happened to her.

95
00:05:33,271 --> 00:05:34,901
It's not your fault.

96
00:05:35,531 --> 00:05:37,741
Yes, it's our fault.

97
00:05:38,301 --> 00:05:39,911
We believed the people
at the market.

98
00:05:40,241 --> 00:05:41,671
It's our fault.

99
00:05:42,881 --> 00:05:44,981
I shouldn't have gone
to the police station.

100
00:05:45,911 --> 00:05:47,911
It just made Dong Suk
hear that nonsense.

101
00:05:48,781 --> 00:05:52,591
Let's not get swayed by that woman.
We should console Dong Suk first.

102
00:05:53,121 --> 00:05:54,591
- Okay.
- Okay.

103
00:06:00,991 --> 00:06:02,661
Are there any other materials
besides this?

104
00:06:02,731 --> 00:06:03,731
I think this material is good.

105
00:06:03,801 --> 00:06:05,661
Let's just see how much you hate it.

106
00:06:11,901 --> 00:06:14,711
This is crazy.
Completely out of his mind.

107
00:06:16,941 --> 00:06:17,941
Excuse me?

108
00:06:19,611 --> 00:06:20,711
It's nothing.

109
00:06:21,051 --> 00:06:24,421
But it's seriously crazy
that you landed CEO Oh Se Rin.

110
00:06:24,481 --> 00:06:26,021
You're amazing as always,
Director Yang.

111
00:06:26,551 --> 00:06:29,221
I know, right?
With most brands, Oh Se Rin...

112
00:06:29,291 --> 00:06:31,121
doesn't even accept
sponsorship proposals.

113
00:06:31,861 --> 00:06:34,331
Director Yang is really incredible.

114
00:06:34,691 --> 00:06:36,101
Still, we don't know for sure yet.

115
00:06:36,131 --> 00:06:38,131
The actor needs to give
the final confirmation.

116
00:06:38,501 --> 00:06:39,531
- Still...
- But...

117
00:06:39,601 --> 00:06:41,631
- it could still happen.
- it could still happen.

118
00:06:42,401 --> 00:06:45,101
- Pelliv.
- Pelliv.

119
00:06:45,541 --> 00:06:46,841
- We need to finalize this quickly.
- Okay.

120
00:06:46,911 --> 00:06:47,911
I think this one looks good.

121
00:06:57,851 --> 00:06:59,121
I like it.

122
00:06:59,751 --> 00:07:01,721
It'll look good on Yoon Seo, right?

123
00:07:02,121 --> 00:07:03,121
Well, we'll have to see it on her.

124
00:07:03,961 --> 00:07:07,661
Well, whether she wears it or not
is up to the actor herself.

125
00:07:07,831 --> 00:07:09,131
Yes, I understand.

126
00:07:09,131 --> 00:07:10,131
Could you wait here?

127
00:07:10,131 --> 00:07:12,101
- We'll let you know as soon.
- Okay, thank you.

128
00:07:12,131 --> 00:07:13,501
Okay. Let's go.

129
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:21,941
- I hope it goes well.
- Right.

130
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:32,351
I freaking love it.

131
00:07:33,621 --> 00:07:36,921
The design and the fit are perfect.

132
00:07:37,261 --> 00:07:38,621
Who brought this in?

133
00:07:39,531 --> 00:07:40,531
Our rookie.

134
00:07:42,761 --> 00:07:43,801
Hey.

135
00:07:44,331 --> 00:07:46,201
You have good taste.

136
00:07:47,001 --> 00:07:49,371
I'm glad you like it.

137
00:07:50,641 --> 00:07:54,341
CEO, from now on,
have her work with me.

138
00:07:56,681 --> 00:07:57,681
Congratulations.

139
00:07:59,481 --> 00:08:01,711
Gosh, congratulations, rookie.

140
00:08:01,881 --> 00:08:03,551
Hey, rookie.
What was your name again?

141
00:08:03,651 --> 00:08:05,881
Eun Bin. Yang Eun Bin.

142
00:08:05,951 --> 00:08:09,921
Good work.
You really saved us, Eun Bin.

143
00:08:10,461 --> 00:08:12,731
- I'll contact Pelliv.
- Okay.

144
00:08:16,501 --> 00:08:18,131
You did so well.

145
00:08:28,711 --> 00:08:30,711
- Eun Bin.
- In-law.

146
00:08:31,041 --> 00:08:33,881
They finally called me
by my name today.

147
00:08:34,681 --> 00:08:36,481
Really? Not rookie?

148
00:08:36,551 --> 00:08:40,651
Yes. I'm not the rookie anymore.
I'm Yang Eun Bin. Eun Bin.

149
00:08:41,991 --> 00:08:44,591
I'm so happy for you.
I knew you'd do great.

150
00:08:44,961 --> 00:08:48,931
Thanks. It's all thanks to you.
I'll definitely treat you. Okay?

151
00:08:49,731 --> 00:08:51,701
When? I'm free right now, today...

152
00:08:54,071 --> 00:08:56,441
Oh, the call dropped.

153
00:09:02,011 --> 00:09:03,011
Yes, CEO Gong.

154
00:09:03,081 --> 00:09:05,611
The Labellin sponsorship
is confirmed.

155
00:09:06,311 --> 00:09:07,311
Really?

156
00:09:17,691 --> 00:09:20,231
Pelliv sponsorship...

157
00:09:22,191 --> 00:09:26,001
- And the model for the clothes?
- Lee Yoon Seo. That variety show.

158
00:09:26,071 --> 00:09:28,371
It'll be featured as part of her
Accidental Camping outfits,

159
00:09:28,431 --> 00:09:31,641
and also for social media exposure,
she has agreed to cooperate fully.

160
00:09:31,971 --> 00:09:32,971
Okay.

161
00:09:32,971 --> 00:09:34,741
- When'll you be at the office...
- I'm busy.

162
00:09:36,581 --> 00:09:39,481
I'm busy too. Honestly, I swear.

163
00:09:39,851 --> 00:09:42,551
CEO Gong, who did they say
is modeling the outfits?

164
00:09:42,881 --> 00:09:45,121
- Lee Yoon Seo.
- Awesome.

165
00:09:45,351 --> 00:09:48,451
CEO Gong, look at this.

166
00:09:48,751 --> 00:09:51,691
Lee Yoon Seo posted our outfit
on her Starstagram story.

167
00:09:52,261 --> 00:09:54,931
She even tagged the Pelliv account.

168
00:09:54,991 --> 00:09:56,861
It looks like
Director Yang negotiated...

169
00:09:56,931 --> 00:10:01,171
- for social media exposure as well.
- I'm so grateful to Director Yang.

170
00:10:01,471 --> 00:10:03,601
I heard he's also in charge of
Taehan Group's rebranding,

171
00:10:03,671 --> 00:10:05,241
yet he's still working so hard
for Pelliv.

172
00:10:05,541 --> 00:10:08,441
- He's truly The Man.
- Loyalty, loyalty. He's The Man.

173
00:10:08,511 --> 00:10:09,511
Loyalty, loyalty. He's The Man.

174
00:10:10,241 --> 00:10:11,681
Wait, how did you do that?
Let me try again.

175
00:10:11,741 --> 00:10:13,111
Loyalty, loyalty, Clappy Man.

176
00:10:14,751 --> 00:10:16,751
This is the proposal
for the corporate story.

177
00:10:16,821 --> 00:10:23,361
(Taehan Group)

178
00:10:23,421 --> 00:10:26,491
"Building a Better Tomorrow?"

179
00:10:26,491 --> 00:10:28,291
Building a better tomorrow?

180
00:10:29,191 --> 00:10:32,501
Are you emphasizing sustainability
and a future-oriented vision?

181
00:10:33,201 --> 00:10:35,801
The corporate materials and website
are also being updated.

182
00:10:36,271 --> 00:10:38,471
I thought all you did was
meet with fashion investors,

183
00:10:38,541 --> 00:10:40,541
but it looks like you've actually
done some work.

184
00:10:40,611 --> 00:10:43,541
Yes. Well, it's been
hectic juggling both.

185
00:10:43,811 --> 00:10:45,141
Is that really all there is to it?

186
00:10:45,211 --> 00:10:48,711
Mind your own business
and do your job properly.

187
00:10:49,011 --> 00:10:52,721
- I am doing it properly.
- That's a laugh. That FG sale...

188
00:10:52,791 --> 00:10:54,391
that you can't even handle properly.

189
00:10:54,451 --> 00:10:56,261
Hey, I'm currently
in the final stages...

190
00:10:57,461 --> 00:10:58,661
I'll be going.

191
00:11:01,831 --> 00:11:03,131
Goodness, that guy...

192
00:11:03,831 --> 00:11:05,501
I really shot myself in the foot.

193
00:11:05,561 --> 00:11:07,631
Why did I bring him here?
What a mess.

194
00:11:09,271 --> 00:11:11,371
Why is the FG sale being delayed?

195
00:11:11,601 --> 00:11:14,171
We're in the final negotiation stage
right now.

196
00:11:14,311 --> 00:11:16,781
We're coordinating the final details
with the acquiring company.

197
00:11:17,581 --> 00:11:21,881
Oh, and here I thought you were
intentionally delaying the sale...

198
00:11:22,081 --> 00:11:24,451
to cook something up
with Director Yang.

199
00:11:25,251 --> 00:11:27,351
What? Why would I do that?
That jerk, every time he sees me...

200
00:11:27,421 --> 00:11:28,651
Can't you see how he
looks down on me?

201
00:11:28,921 --> 00:11:30,621
Okay. I get it.

202
00:11:31,621 --> 00:11:33,731
I'll get the absolute highest price
for the sale,

203
00:11:33,791 --> 00:11:35,491
so please just wait a little longer.

204
00:11:35,491 --> 00:11:37,401
- Right.
- Right.

205
00:11:38,961 --> 00:11:42,271
(Taehan Group)

206
00:11:43,841 --> 00:11:44,841
Director Baek,

207
00:11:45,471 --> 00:11:47,571
could we have been mistaken?

208
00:11:48,271 --> 00:11:49,941
Time will tell.

209
00:11:50,341 --> 00:11:53,151
- Speed up the Landmark project.
- Yes, sir.

210
00:11:53,311 --> 00:11:56,651
(Director Baek Won Gyu)

211
00:11:59,181 --> 00:12:02,591
So, have you given
Councilor Hwang an answer?

212
00:12:02,891 --> 00:12:03,891
No.

213
00:12:04,661 --> 00:12:06,121
You haven't given me
your decision yet.

214
00:12:06,831 --> 00:12:07,991
When it comes to
matters of the market,

215
00:12:08,631 --> 00:12:10,701
I follow the Merchants' Association
President's opinion.

216
00:12:12,301 --> 00:12:15,731
Should we just let them
bulldoze the market?

217
00:12:16,871 --> 00:12:17,871
Jeong Han.

218
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:20,841
I'm just angry at the people
in the market. That's all.

219
00:12:21,611 --> 00:12:23,411
I've spent my whole life
helping them,

220
00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:25,911
and now it feels like
I've lived my life all wrong.

221
00:12:26,511 --> 00:12:29,551
It's our fault for believing
the rumors that woman spread,

222
00:12:30,081 --> 00:12:31,921
not the market people's, right?

223
00:12:32,991 --> 00:12:34,421
Yes, I know.

224
00:12:35,991 --> 00:12:38,621
I'm just saying that
because I'm upset.

225
00:12:43,861 --> 00:12:47,271
Why are you sorry?
I'm the one who should be.

226
00:12:49,471 --> 00:12:50,471
I...

227
00:12:52,071 --> 00:12:56,441
If only I hadn't doubted In Ok,
this wouldn't have happened.

228
00:12:57,741 --> 00:13:00,711
You must have spent
the last 30 years hating me.

229
00:13:01,751 --> 00:13:02,751
I did.

230
00:13:04,651 --> 00:13:07,891
For 30 years, our families...

231
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:09,921
were enemies.

232
00:13:11,191 --> 00:13:12,321
But...

233
00:13:13,091 --> 00:13:14,561
we cleared up the misunderstanding,

234
00:13:15,361 --> 00:13:16,861
and became in-laws.

235
00:13:17,561 --> 00:13:20,331
So from now on,
you need to take responsibility,

236
00:13:20,401 --> 00:13:22,031
and look after our families.

237
00:13:23,501 --> 00:13:24,501
Me?

238
00:13:24,901 --> 00:13:27,311
- And what will you be doing?
- Me?

239
00:13:28,371 --> 00:13:31,281
I've done my part.
Now it's your turn.

240
00:13:31,381 --> 00:13:35,311
We're in this together, man.
Don't try to dump it all on me.

241
00:13:37,551 --> 00:13:39,991
Goodness. Oh, my.

242
00:13:42,991 --> 00:13:45,291
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

243
00:13:45,491 --> 00:13:47,591
Because I went
to the police station,

244
00:13:48,031 --> 00:13:50,431
you're the one who had to hear
all that nonsense, Dong Suk.

245
00:13:50,861 --> 00:13:52,761
Not at all.

246
00:13:53,831 --> 00:13:56,871
And I'm going to do as you said,
Mother.

247
00:13:57,141 --> 00:14:00,311
I'm really going to forget
about that woman and be happy.

248
00:14:01,741 --> 00:14:04,711
Good. That's my daughter-in-law.

249
00:14:06,611 --> 00:14:09,251
You're a very strong person, Mother.

250
00:14:09,581 --> 00:14:13,651
Father, when I saw her talking
to that woman at the police station,

251
00:14:13,721 --> 00:14:15,121
I was so surprised.

252
00:14:15,621 --> 00:14:16,691
You were?

253
00:14:17,021 --> 00:14:21,331
Yes. That woman was so furious
she was trembling.

254
00:14:22,461 --> 00:14:26,001
Thirty years of living without a husband
makes you tough, doesn't it?

255
00:14:26,061 --> 00:14:27,071
Yes.

256
00:14:28,971 --> 00:14:33,811
Oh, by the way, Dae Han stopped by
his in-laws' place.

257
00:14:34,511 --> 00:14:35,511
Ji Hu?

258
00:14:36,441 --> 00:14:37,641
Did something happen?

259
00:14:40,111 --> 00:14:42,011
- A younger sibling?
- Yes.

260
00:14:42,281 --> 00:14:45,051
Would you be okay
if you had a younger sibling?

261
00:14:46,251 --> 00:14:48,221
Do I have a say in it?

262
00:14:48,691 --> 00:14:50,461
Of course. Isn't that obvious?

263
00:14:50,991 --> 00:14:52,921
Why? Am I the one
who has to raise them?

264
00:14:53,361 --> 00:14:54,561
What kind of question is that?

265
00:14:54,961 --> 00:14:56,131
I'm having this baby
to raise myself.

266
00:14:56,231 --> 00:14:58,601
- Why would you raise them?
- I heard you had a hard time...

267
00:14:58,661 --> 00:15:00,401
raising your nieces and nephews,
Stepdad.

268
00:15:00,671 --> 00:15:03,641
Right, I hadn't thought of that.

269
00:15:04,771 --> 00:15:06,511
If it gets too hard to raise them,
I can just leave them...

270
00:15:06,571 --> 00:15:07,611
with my nieces and nephews. Right?

271
00:15:10,311 --> 00:15:11,311
Ji Hu.

272
00:15:12,041 --> 00:15:13,851
Think carefully before you answer.

273
00:15:14,281 --> 00:15:15,851
If a baby brother or sister
comes along,

274
00:15:15,911 --> 00:15:17,421
the whole family will dote
on the baby,

275
00:15:17,551 --> 00:15:18,851
so you might feel left out.

276
00:15:19,851 --> 00:15:23,421
Please, stop paying attention to me
and just focus on the baby.

277
00:15:24,691 --> 00:15:26,061
You're really okay with that?

278
00:15:26,321 --> 00:15:29,531
It might be hard at Mom's age,
so you should try twice as hard.

279
00:15:29,591 --> 00:15:30,601
Try hard?

280
00:15:32,131 --> 00:15:33,571
You can leave that to me.

281
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:36,271
Hurry up and eat your watermelon.

282
00:15:38,441 --> 00:15:39,441
Thanks.

283
00:15:49,651 --> 00:15:51,051
You spent your lives being fooled,

284
00:15:51,051 --> 00:15:52,581
just believing
what people told you, right?

285
00:15:53,621 --> 00:15:57,661
You pathetic, naive fools.

286
00:16:01,331 --> 00:16:03,501
You're upset, but you're just
acting tough, aren't you?

287
00:16:05,261 --> 00:16:06,731
I'm not upset.

288
00:16:07,331 --> 00:16:08,871
Are you really okay?

289
00:16:09,531 --> 00:16:10,871
I have to be.

290
00:16:11,241 --> 00:16:13,271
Goodness, do you really have to?

291
00:16:13,841 --> 00:16:14,971
I have to.

292
00:16:15,771 --> 00:16:16,781
I...

293
00:16:17,711 --> 00:16:20,781
I'm never going to live the way
that woman wants me to.

294
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:22,751
I, Na Seon Hae,

295
00:16:23,581 --> 00:16:26,651
am a strong person
who will never be shaken.

296
00:16:34,031 --> 00:16:36,131
He hasn't shown his face
at all today.

297
00:16:37,261 --> 00:16:39,261
Why am I waiting for him?
I must be crazy.

298
00:16:43,741 --> 00:16:46,811
- Still working?
- Oh, you're here.

299
00:16:47,271 --> 00:16:50,981
Right. What a warm welcome.

300
00:16:51,081 --> 00:16:52,511
You missed me, right?

301
00:16:53,111 --> 00:16:54,111
Who says?

302
00:16:54,911 --> 00:16:59,551
Let's be honest about our feelings.
After last night's intense kiss,

303
00:16:59,621 --> 00:17:02,691
- you kept thinking of me, right?
- Intense, my foot.

304
00:17:02,691 --> 00:17:03,761
It was just a punishment.
That's all.

305
00:17:03,761 --> 00:17:07,291
- Zero impact.
- Liar.

306
00:17:07,691 --> 00:17:10,231
I could hear your heart pounding.

307
00:17:10,661 --> 00:17:12,831
Keep the cheesy lines to yourself.

308
00:17:13,401 --> 00:17:15,871
So what have you been so busy with?

309
00:17:15,871 --> 00:17:16,871
Oh, that.

310
00:17:17,641 --> 00:17:18,801
Securing an investment.

311
00:17:19,341 --> 00:17:23,041
- You got one? From where?
- Clairmont Expansion in Paris.

312
00:17:23,211 --> 00:17:24,281
Clairmont?

313
00:17:24,681 --> 00:17:28,481
- Isn't that we got funded at FG?
- That's right.

314
00:17:29,011 --> 00:17:31,281
The connections I made
back at FG paid off.

315
00:17:31,721 --> 00:17:34,221
Other investment firms are also
in positive discussions.

316
00:17:34,291 --> 00:17:35,551
So? I did a good job, right?

317
00:17:36,121 --> 00:17:40,431
I thought you were all talk,
but I guess you're not.

318
00:17:40,491 --> 00:17:42,061
So annoying.

319
00:17:43,201 --> 00:17:45,731
But why are you expanding
things so much?

320
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:47,771
Just tell me already.

321
00:17:48,331 --> 00:17:51,801
Just wait a little longer.
We're almost there. Gosh, I'm tired.

322
00:17:52,671 --> 00:17:53,771
Then you should've gone home
to rest.

323
00:17:53,841 --> 00:17:55,241
Did you just come to brag
about your investment?

324
00:17:56,341 --> 00:17:58,111
No matter how tired I am,
I have to see...

325
00:17:58,181 --> 00:17:59,541
your face at least once a day.

326
00:18:01,911 --> 00:18:02,911
Why?

327
00:18:05,021 --> 00:18:06,221
That's a good question.

328
00:18:07,851 --> 00:18:10,261
I guess I just blurted out
some nonsense.

329
00:18:13,561 --> 00:18:15,631
Oh, my. Hold on...

330
00:18:16,531 --> 00:18:18,131
You told me not to get close.

331
00:18:18,261 --> 00:18:20,971
Hey, you're bleeding.
It's just human decency, you know.

332
00:18:21,031 --> 00:18:22,871
Oh, wait, here, here.

333
00:18:23,671 --> 00:18:24,841
I don't think so.

334
00:18:25,171 --> 00:18:28,911
- You've been weird since we kissed.
- Goodness...

335
00:18:30,741 --> 00:18:32,441
They say you should tilt
your head down for a nosebleed.

336
00:18:32,511 --> 00:18:34,251
Don't you dare lift it.

337
00:18:34,911 --> 00:18:37,481
- I lifted it.
- Oh, honestly...

338
00:18:37,751 --> 00:18:38,751
Lifted.

339
00:18:45,661 --> 00:18:49,591
Wait,
why does everyone look so shocked?

340
00:18:50,061 --> 00:18:51,931
Wait, Dong Suk, is it for real?

341
00:18:52,931 --> 00:18:54,531
Dae Han... Dong Suk...

342
00:18:55,031 --> 00:18:57,901
Hey, hey, did I hear that right?

343
00:18:58,171 --> 00:19:01,211
No, Jeong Han.
It's exactly as you heard.

344
00:19:02,941 --> 00:19:05,341
We're going to try for a baby.

345
00:19:06,411 --> 00:19:10,221
Hey, Gong Dae Han.
You said you wanted a baby?

346
00:19:10,451 --> 00:19:13,121
It'll be hard on you
at your age, Dae Han.

347
00:19:13,251 --> 00:19:17,391
Hey, come on, man. Don't be greedy.
It'll be hard on Dong Suk.

348
00:19:17,921 --> 00:19:20,191
See? I told you we'd get an earful.

349
00:19:20,831 --> 00:19:23,701
No. I'm the one who said
I wanted a baby.

350
00:19:25,061 --> 00:19:27,031
Aunt Dong Suk, are you serious?

351
00:19:27,331 --> 00:19:31,241
I really want a baby.
One that looks just like Uncle.

352
00:19:31,371 --> 00:19:34,171
So your wish is coming true, Uncle?

353
00:19:35,311 --> 00:19:37,711
But don't get your hopes up
too high, everyone.

354
00:19:39,181 --> 00:19:40,611
It's just that we're a little old...

355
00:19:40,781 --> 00:19:43,981
Yes, we just want to give it a shot.

356
00:19:44,321 --> 00:19:46,521
It would be so wonderful
if it happens.

357
00:19:47,251 --> 00:19:48,821
I know, right?

358
00:19:49,451 --> 00:19:51,061
Everyone's been so down lately.

359
00:19:51,121 --> 00:19:53,591
It's nice to see everyone smiling
for a change.

360
00:19:54,861 --> 00:19:59,001
Father, I will give it my all
as long as I have the strength.

361
00:19:59,001 --> 00:20:00,601
- Oh my.
- Hey.

362
00:20:01,201 --> 00:20:03,941
No drinking starting today.
And exercise every day, you hear?

363
00:20:04,001 --> 00:20:06,101
- It's okay.
- Unbelievable...

364
00:20:06,771 --> 00:20:09,611
Is my aunt really having a baby?
Is that even possible?

365
00:20:09,811 --> 00:20:11,681
Well, if they try, you never know.

366
00:20:11,981 --> 00:20:14,181
At their age?

367
00:20:14,181 --> 00:20:15,581
They're just setting themselves up
for heartbreak.

368
00:20:16,181 --> 00:20:17,181
Well...

369
00:20:18,151 --> 00:20:21,651
Hey, what is Father
doing over there?

370
00:20:23,621 --> 00:20:25,921
- Father, no. Please give it here.
- Let go.

371
00:20:26,731 --> 00:20:28,361
I'm just going to eat what I want.

372
00:20:28,731 --> 00:20:29,791
Grandfather, what's with you?

373
00:20:29,861 --> 00:20:31,401
Are you going through
a rebellious phase?

374
00:20:31,631 --> 00:20:34,131
You know perfectly well
that flour is bad...

375
00:20:34,201 --> 00:20:35,931
for your dermatitis, Father.

376
00:20:36,001 --> 00:20:37,671
When are you going to become
a city council member?

377
00:20:38,501 --> 00:20:41,641
Father, the nomination review
hasn't even happened yet.

378
00:20:42,711 --> 00:20:44,911
You're pressuring me day and night.

379
00:20:45,711 --> 00:20:47,251
Gosh, this is so much pressure.

380
00:20:47,611 --> 00:20:49,811
Grandfather, you have to say
your next line.

381
00:20:50,321 --> 00:20:53,021
- Now all I need to see is...
- Now all I need to see is...

382
00:20:53,021 --> 00:20:55,021
- Hyun Bin get married.
- Hyun Bin get married.

383
00:20:55,091 --> 00:20:56,291
That's right. Keep at him.

384
00:20:56,521 --> 00:20:59,721
Father, I really can't do this.

385
00:20:59,991 --> 00:21:01,691
I'm just saying to set him up
with any woman.

386
00:21:03,331 --> 00:21:04,331
Father.

387
00:21:04,401 --> 00:21:06,901
Have I asked you for that much?
How can you say you can't do it?

388
00:21:07,031 --> 00:21:11,101
Okay, Father.
I'll see what I can do.

389
00:21:22,711 --> 00:21:24,551
Oh, are you
really going to finish this?

390
00:21:28,291 --> 00:21:30,091
The rate Pelliv's
Starstagram followers...

391
00:21:30,161 --> 00:21:31,161
are growing is insane.

392
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:33,861
How are the pre-orders doing?

393
00:21:33,861 --> 00:21:35,391
They should be showing results
by now.

394
00:21:35,531 --> 00:21:39,331
- All pre-orders have been sold out.
- Really?

395
00:21:39,931 --> 00:21:42,001
The response was faster
than I expected.

396
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:46,671
Hey, Pacu Nacho.

397
00:21:47,571 --> 00:21:49,471
Did you hear that
Pelliv is doing well?

398
00:21:50,141 --> 00:21:52,511
I'm not even jealous
of the Taehan Fashion Division.

399
00:21:55,081 --> 00:21:56,151
You want me to come where?

400
00:21:56,751 --> 00:21:59,051
I'm not going.
I wouldn't even turn that way...

401
00:22:01,751 --> 00:22:03,121
to take a leak.

402
00:22:03,661 --> 00:22:04,721
Look, I said I'm not going.

403
00:22:05,261 --> 00:22:06,861
Hello? Hey.

404
00:22:09,431 --> 00:22:11,031
Where did he want you to come to?

405
00:22:11,961 --> 00:22:14,301
To Taehan. With you.

406
00:22:15,771 --> 00:22:17,001
Why me?

407
00:22:21,511 --> 00:22:24,241
(Taehan Group)

408
00:22:25,711 --> 00:22:26,741
Director Baek.

409
00:22:27,211 --> 00:22:28,651
An emergency board meeting
has been called.

410
00:22:29,111 --> 00:22:30,651
Who called a board meeting?

411
00:22:30,951 --> 00:22:32,481
Vice President Hwangbo Hye Su.

412
00:22:33,181 --> 00:22:34,191
What?

413
00:22:35,721 --> 00:22:37,061
You didn't know about this?

414
00:22:37,461 --> 00:22:39,391
No.
This is the first I'm hearing of it.

415
00:22:42,661 --> 00:22:45,931
(Taehan Group)

416
00:22:52,601 --> 00:22:54,741
What on earth is she trying to do?

417
00:22:55,771 --> 00:22:58,241
Gosh, I'm dying to know myself.

418
00:23:01,011 --> 00:23:02,011
I am Yang Hyun Bin,

419
00:23:02,081 --> 00:23:04,551
the Executive Director
of the Strategic Planning Division.

420
00:23:05,521 --> 00:23:06,951
On behalf of the chairman,

421
00:23:07,021 --> 00:23:09,251
I will be leading
today's board meeting.

422
00:23:10,761 --> 00:23:12,091
The first item on the agenda...

423
00:23:12,591 --> 00:23:14,691
is the approval
for the establishment...

424
00:23:14,761 --> 00:23:16,031
of Taehan Fashion.

425
00:23:20,371 --> 00:23:21,831
What is he talking about?

426
00:23:26,911 --> 00:23:29,771
What is this nonsense about
establishing Taehan Fashion?

427
00:23:29,941 --> 00:23:32,041
I mean, we already shut down
the Fashion Division,

428
00:23:32,111 --> 00:23:34,551
- and FG was sold.
- The sale fell through.

429
00:23:34,611 --> 00:23:37,081
FG will be transferred
to Taehan Fashion.

430
00:23:38,081 --> 00:23:42,251
- Now the pieces fall into place.
- What?

431
00:23:42,851 --> 00:23:44,261
Did you know about this?

432
00:23:44,591 --> 00:23:46,161
I just had a hunch.

433
00:23:46,761 --> 00:23:47,891
Call a board meeting for me.

434
00:23:48,391 --> 00:23:50,701
The Fashion Division
that Director Baek shut down,

435
00:23:50,861 --> 00:23:51,961
I'll revive it
as an independent entity,

436
00:23:52,031 --> 00:23:53,031
Taehan Fashion.

437
00:23:53,331 --> 00:23:54,431
Do you really think that'll work?

438
00:23:54,871 --> 00:23:56,941
You think Director Baek
will stand by and let that happen?

439
00:23:58,341 --> 00:24:00,311
The Fashion Division
was a failed venture...

440
00:24:00,371 --> 00:24:01,641
that we already shut down.

441
00:24:02,111 --> 00:24:03,811
Do you think
simply changing the name...

442
00:24:03,881 --> 00:24:06,081
will make it competitive
when it wasn't before?

443
00:24:09,511 --> 00:24:11,381
If you look at the documents
in front of you,

444
00:24:11,781 --> 00:24:14,691
you'll see the new investment plan,
the overseas sales plan,

445
00:24:14,751 --> 00:24:16,691
the production line construction status,

446
00:24:16,851 --> 00:24:20,061
and the brand's growth indicators.

447
00:24:24,501 --> 00:24:28,301
Taehan Fashion's business
will be centered on Pelliv,

448
00:24:28,371 --> 00:24:30,441
a new brand by the whole Design Team
of the Fashion Division.

449
00:24:30,641 --> 00:24:32,501
It will expand
its business operations...

450
00:24:32,571 --> 00:24:33,571
together with FG.

451
00:24:35,371 --> 00:24:38,011
CEO Gong,
are you really okay with this?

452
00:24:38,641 --> 00:24:40,211
Pelliv is yours, isn't it?

453
00:24:40,851 --> 00:24:44,421
No. Pelliv belongs to everyone
in the Fashion Division.

454
00:24:44,751 --> 00:24:47,391
Besides, none of my own money
went into the launch.

455
00:24:47,991 --> 00:24:48,991
Thank you.

456
00:24:50,191 --> 00:24:51,221
I am...

457
00:24:51,821 --> 00:24:53,591
just happy I could be the spark...

458
00:24:53,691 --> 00:24:55,661
that helps revive
the Fashion Division.

459
00:24:57,261 --> 00:25:01,071
Immediately upon its release,
all of Pelliv's pre-orders sold out,

460
00:25:01,471 --> 00:25:03,501
and we've also secured
global investment.

461
00:25:04,001 --> 00:25:05,141
If you review the materials,

462
00:25:05,571 --> 00:25:09,211
you will see for yourselves
how competitive Taehan Fashion is.

463
00:25:12,141 --> 00:25:14,951
(Taehan Group)

464
00:25:25,821 --> 00:25:27,231
Executive Director
Hwangbo Jun Hyeok.

465
00:25:28,191 --> 00:25:30,531
As the one who led the shutdown
of the Fashion Division,

466
00:25:31,231 --> 00:25:34,271
please share your opinion
on this absurd proposal.

467
00:25:34,901 --> 00:25:37,271
Yes.

468
00:25:41,341 --> 00:25:43,781
Yes. This is Hwangbo Jun Hyeok.

469
00:25:45,441 --> 00:25:47,711
The problem is Hwangbo Jun Hyeok.

470
00:25:48,351 --> 00:25:49,351
That's right.

471
00:25:49,411 --> 00:25:51,151
That brat got rid of
the Fashion Division,

472
00:25:51,221 --> 00:25:52,321
our father's passion project.

473
00:25:52,581 --> 00:25:55,251
The board was completely on his side
back then, too.

474
00:25:55,321 --> 00:25:56,391
What's different now?

475
00:26:04,061 --> 00:26:06,731
(Taehan Group)

476
00:26:11,041 --> 00:26:12,601
- What?
- My gosh.

477
00:26:15,071 --> 00:26:16,311
Yes.

478
00:26:16,671 --> 00:26:18,811
Director Yang Hyun Bin's proposal.

479
00:26:22,411 --> 00:26:24,021
- I am in favor of it.
- What?

480
00:26:24,081 --> 00:26:25,121
In favor?

481
00:26:25,981 --> 00:26:27,751
I thought he was supposed to be
against it.

482
00:26:29,221 --> 00:26:30,461
What do you think you're doing?

483
00:26:32,191 --> 00:26:34,131
Taehan's fashion business was...

484
00:26:34,191 --> 00:26:36,691
the late Chairman's founding business,

485
00:26:36,761 --> 00:26:39,361
and it is the root
and identity of our group.

486
00:26:39,861 --> 00:26:42,101
Since the market
recognizes its value,

487
00:26:42,171 --> 00:26:44,541
I have no reason
to oppose it any longer.

488
00:26:47,971 --> 00:26:49,071
This jerk...

489
00:26:49,911 --> 00:26:51,211
What are you after?

490
00:26:51,811 --> 00:26:53,511
What? Are you trying to become
the CEO...

491
00:26:53,581 --> 00:26:54,981
of Taehan Fashion or something?

492
00:26:56,951 --> 00:26:59,121
If the establishment proposal
is approved,

493
00:26:59,221 --> 00:27:01,591
we'll also proceed
to the appointment of a CEO.

494
00:27:01,991 --> 00:27:03,321
The candidate for CEO...

495
00:27:04,521 --> 00:27:06,521
is Vice President Hwangbo Hye Su.

496
00:27:34,751 --> 00:27:37,721
Hey, you were on our side?

497
00:27:38,021 --> 00:27:40,461
Hey, come on. Of course I was.

498
00:27:40,961 --> 00:27:43,461
Good work, Undercover Mr. Park.

499
00:27:44,301 --> 00:27:45,301
Hyeok!

500
00:27:46,231 --> 00:27:47,231
My little brother.

501
00:27:47,971 --> 00:27:49,131
Let go of me. Seriously, okay?

502
00:27:49,201 --> 00:27:51,241
If I knew I'd get beaten
and cursed out like this,

503
00:27:51,301 --> 00:27:52,701
I never would've done it.

504
00:27:52,771 --> 00:27:56,011
Hey, you... Jun Hyeok...

505
00:27:56,141 --> 00:27:57,541
Right.

506
00:27:58,711 --> 00:28:03,251
But, even if Jun Hyeok
is on our side, that...

507
00:28:03,311 --> 00:28:07,191
Ju Ah. Who do you think I am?
In the meantime,

508
00:28:07,251 --> 00:28:09,851
I got all the board members
on my side.

509
00:28:10,291 --> 00:28:12,591
Then we will proceed with the vote.

510
00:28:12,991 --> 00:28:15,731
All those in favor of
establishing Taehan Fashion,

511
00:28:16,391 --> 00:28:17,661
please raise your hands.

512
00:28:54,831 --> 00:28:58,541
Have a safe trip.

513
00:29:17,561 --> 00:29:20,661
The fashion business
is coming back to Taehan. No.

514
00:29:21,031 --> 00:29:24,601
- Taehan Fashion.
- What's wrong? Speak clearly.

515
00:29:24,701 --> 00:29:27,031
You fool.
Pelliv was just a smokescreen...

516
00:29:27,101 --> 00:29:29,631
- from Director Yang.
- Come on, how is that possible?

517
00:29:29,701 --> 00:29:31,771
Hwangbo Jun Hyeok
would've gotten in our way.

518
00:29:32,471 --> 00:29:34,111
Well, the thing is...

519
00:29:34,411 --> 00:29:37,211
- Hwangbo Jun Hyeok was on our side.
- What?

520
00:29:37,941 --> 00:29:39,111
Since when?

521
00:29:41,211 --> 00:29:42,411
From the very beginning.

522
00:29:44,351 --> 00:29:47,251
You're really telling me to become
one of Director Baek's men?

523
00:29:48,151 --> 00:29:52,161
Yes. Director Baek will call
an emergency board meeting soon.

524
00:29:52,691 --> 00:29:55,361
He'll definitely propose
selling off FG,

525
00:29:56,131 --> 00:29:57,901
and when he does,
you must side with Director Baek.

526
00:29:58,031 --> 00:30:01,701
And volunteer to take charge
of the FG sale yourself.

527
00:30:02,301 --> 00:30:05,141
But why are you asking me
to do something like that?

528
00:30:05,201 --> 00:30:09,071
While I launch a successful brand
through Ju Ah,

529
00:30:09,141 --> 00:30:10,611
I need you to delay FG's sale...

530
00:30:10,681 --> 00:30:12,341
for as long as possible
to buy us time.

531
00:30:13,141 --> 00:30:18,021
Wait, but why do the work twice?
Can't we just block the sale of FG?

532
00:30:19,421 --> 00:30:21,421
Even if we block the sale of FG,

533
00:30:21,491 --> 00:30:23,321
Director Baek
will eventually shut down...

534
00:30:23,391 --> 00:30:24,391
the fashion business.

535
00:30:25,161 --> 00:30:26,321
I'm going to make it so...

536
00:30:26,391 --> 00:30:28,361
Director Baek
can never touch it again.

537
00:30:28,461 --> 00:30:30,061
I'm going to spin off
the fashion business...

538
00:30:30,131 --> 00:30:31,331
into an independent corporation.

539
00:30:34,971 --> 00:30:39,071
Still, you could've told me
beforehand.

540
00:30:39,271 --> 00:30:41,841
If you had known, Vice President,
it would've been so obvious...

541
00:30:41,911 --> 00:30:43,571
that Director Baek
would have found out.

542
00:30:44,341 --> 00:30:45,341
That's true.

543
00:30:45,711 --> 00:30:46,741
Still...

544
00:30:47,011 --> 00:30:48,851
You two should apologize to me.

545
00:30:49,511 --> 00:30:51,581
You little brat.

546
00:30:52,121 --> 00:30:53,181
"Sister?"

547
00:30:53,921 --> 00:30:55,051
Why did you hit me, sister?

548
00:30:55,121 --> 00:30:57,891
Don't call me that. I don't have
a younger brother like you.

549
00:31:02,361 --> 00:31:03,491
Hey, this is attempted murder.

550
00:31:03,561 --> 00:31:06,501
Too bad it was just an attempt.
I was trying to kill you.

551
00:31:06,961 --> 00:31:08,371
I'm sorry, my little brother.

552
00:31:08,701 --> 00:31:11,671
- Should I get on my knees and...
- Forget it. Goodness.

553
00:31:13,571 --> 00:31:17,211
By the way,
what were the Chairman's last words?

554
00:31:32,161 --> 00:31:34,291
Thank you for coming...

555
00:31:35,091 --> 00:31:36,531
Thank...

556
00:31:36,831 --> 00:31:39,231
Thank you, my son.

557
00:31:43,171 --> 00:31:44,541
Yes, Father.

558
00:31:51,241 --> 00:31:52,881
Protect...

559
00:31:54,081 --> 00:31:55,751
Your sister...

560
00:31:59,021 --> 00:32:00,021
Taehan...

561
00:32:00,821 --> 00:32:02,421
Fashion...

562
00:32:06,191 --> 00:32:07,861
Protect it...

563
00:32:09,291 --> 00:32:10,291
Yes.

564
00:32:11,001 --> 00:32:12,701
I promise I will.

565
00:32:17,071 --> 00:32:19,601
Father.

566
00:32:20,341 --> 00:32:23,271
Father, please wake up.

567
00:32:24,211 --> 00:32:26,081
Dad, don't go.

568
00:32:27,311 --> 00:32:28,381
Dad.

569
00:32:30,481 --> 00:32:33,821
Well, I've honored
my father's last wish.

570
00:32:34,291 --> 00:32:36,991
To protect Taehan Fashion
and to protect my sister.

571
00:32:38,361 --> 00:32:42,661
Hyeok. Oh, my dear brother.
Oh, what a relief.

572
00:32:46,401 --> 00:32:50,741
Oh, my Hyeok.

573
00:32:59,881 --> 00:33:01,311
It's been a while
since I've been here.

574
00:33:02,111 --> 00:33:03,381
Don't I get any credit?

575
00:33:03,851 --> 00:33:06,221
I kept the promise I made
when we broke up.

576
00:33:06,921 --> 00:33:08,391
You did well, Yang Hyun Bin.

577
00:33:09,321 --> 00:33:10,421
And...

578
00:33:10,891 --> 00:33:12,361
thank you, really.

579
00:33:12,661 --> 00:33:14,061
Gosh...

580
00:33:14,561 --> 00:33:17,561
Man, I went through a lot
just to hear you say that.

581
00:33:22,131 --> 00:33:24,401
What about you? Are you coming back?

582
00:33:24,801 --> 00:33:28,711
No way. I quit my job
just so I wouldn't have to see you.

583
00:33:28,771 --> 00:33:30,011
Why would I come back?

584
00:33:33,811 --> 00:33:35,051
Pelliv...

585
00:33:35,381 --> 00:33:38,521
It's a brand made with your designs.
Don't you feel it's a waste?

586
00:33:39,481 --> 00:33:40,551
No.

587
00:33:41,191 --> 00:33:44,391
I overcame my fears
with this launch,

588
00:33:44,721 --> 00:33:47,961
and most importantly,
I gained confidence in my designs.

589
00:33:48,931 --> 00:33:51,201
If you come to Taehan,
I'll guarantee you'll keep...

590
00:33:51,261 --> 00:33:52,761
full authority over your designs.

591
00:33:53,001 --> 00:33:54,871
You'll get performance incentives,
of course,

592
00:33:54,931 --> 00:33:57,131
and I'll put you in charge
of all collection planning.

593
00:33:59,301 --> 00:34:00,501
And if I don't come back?

594
00:34:01,541 --> 00:34:05,441
Taehan will fully compensate you
for the rights to your designs.

595
00:34:05,711 --> 00:34:08,811
Whatever you choose,
I'll make sure you don't lose out.

596
00:34:09,281 --> 00:34:10,681
The decision is yours.

597
00:34:17,861 --> 00:34:20,291
Are you looking for
anything in particular?

598
00:34:20,361 --> 00:34:22,531
We have more new arrivals
at the front.

599
00:34:22,591 --> 00:34:25,401
- Okay, thank you.
- Thank you.

600
00:34:27,531 --> 00:34:28,531
So pretty.

601
00:34:28,601 --> 00:34:29,701
Go on, pick anything you want. Okay?

602
00:34:30,171 --> 00:34:32,601
Of course. This is the first gift
for your parents, Jin Ah.

603
00:34:32,701 --> 00:34:35,341
Yes, I will gladly pay for it.

604
00:34:35,411 --> 00:34:37,541
Okay, in that case...

605
00:34:40,611 --> 00:34:41,851
How about this one?

606
00:34:43,881 --> 00:34:46,581
It's clean and looks cool.
It's nice, don't you think?

607
00:34:47,121 --> 00:34:48,521
I think they'll like it.

608
00:34:49,421 --> 00:34:51,361
Then let's get this one.

609
00:34:51,661 --> 00:34:54,491
- Can you gift wrap this?
- Yes, we can.

610
00:34:55,391 --> 00:34:57,601
- I'll get that ready for you.
- Thank you.

611
00:34:59,061 --> 00:35:03,031
My hand is so dazzling,
it's hard to choose.

612
00:35:04,171 --> 00:35:06,171
In my eyes,
you're much more dazzling, Jin Ah.

613
00:35:06,241 --> 00:35:07,941
Oh, come on.

614
00:35:09,471 --> 00:35:13,081
But I can't even show off
this pretty ring. It's such a shame.

615
00:35:13,181 --> 00:35:16,581
Why can't you show it off?
Is something going on at the clinic?

616
00:35:16,651 --> 00:35:20,221
Well... things at the clinic
have felt off lately.

617
00:35:20,681 --> 00:35:22,791
But they've already arrested
Jo Mi Hyang. Why?

618
00:35:23,221 --> 00:35:25,891
I think she's been traumatized.

619
00:35:26,221 --> 00:35:29,061
Because of those rumors?

620
00:35:29,261 --> 00:35:33,361
Yes, I think what people said
really hurt her.

621
00:35:34,931 --> 00:35:36,501
Oh, dear.

622
00:35:36,771 --> 00:35:39,141
Hey, did you hear?

623
00:35:39,301 --> 00:35:42,771
You know Mr. and Mrs. Choi
from the jewelry store?

624
00:35:42,841 --> 00:35:45,781
- They're getting a divorce.
- Why? They seemed happy together.

625
00:35:45,841 --> 00:35:47,181
I don't know. Apparently,
Mr. Choi's wife...

626
00:35:47,241 --> 00:35:48,751
was attending classes
at the community center...

627
00:35:48,811 --> 00:35:51,781
- and she had an affair.
- Really? Who saw it happen?

628
00:35:51,851 --> 00:35:53,181
I don't know. But come on.

629
00:35:53,251 --> 00:35:55,351
Where there's smoke,
there's fire, right?

630
00:35:55,421 --> 00:35:58,161
- Oh, I knew it.
- It was obvious.

631
00:35:58,661 --> 00:36:00,721
You need your physical therapy today
before you leave.

632
00:36:01,291 --> 00:36:03,961
Yes, I have to listen to you.

633
00:36:04,301 --> 00:36:07,031
- I can't leave it like last time...
- Mr. Gong.

634
00:36:07,331 --> 00:36:09,201
That patient's trapezius...

635
00:36:09,201 --> 00:36:11,041
and the muscles
around her rotator cuff,

636
00:36:11,141 --> 00:36:13,401
are very stiff,
so please take good care of her.

637
00:36:13,971 --> 00:36:16,871
Oh, my. Our dear Dr. Gong,

638
00:36:17,141 --> 00:36:21,111
- aren't you feeling well?
- I'll see you next time.

639
00:36:21,811 --> 00:36:25,121
Yes. Let's go. Right this way. Yes.

640
00:36:26,151 --> 00:36:27,721
Okay, Ma'am.
Please lie down over here.

641
00:36:28,491 --> 00:36:29,491
Dr. Gong.

642
00:36:30,491 --> 00:36:33,591
- The senior doctor is here too.
- Hello.

643
00:36:34,391 --> 00:36:37,291
Here, I brought
some spicy squid salad.

644
00:36:38,231 --> 00:36:39,531
It's good mixed with rice.

645
00:36:39,601 --> 00:36:43,471
No, that's all right. Please,
take it back and have it yourself.

646
00:36:43,871 --> 00:36:46,871
Why? But you like this.

647
00:36:47,341 --> 00:36:48,911
I won't be accepting gifts
like this anymore.

648
00:36:49,311 --> 00:36:51,441
So please don't go to the trouble
of bringing them.

649
00:36:53,281 --> 00:36:54,281
Oh, dear.

650
00:36:55,981 --> 00:36:59,921
Well, could you take it then?

651
00:37:00,951 --> 00:37:01,951
Well, this...

652
00:37:05,391 --> 00:37:06,391
So,

653
00:37:07,291 --> 00:37:09,661
- have you made up your mind?
- Yes.

654
00:37:11,231 --> 00:37:14,031
Just get the nomination
and tear down the market.

655
00:37:14,801 --> 00:37:16,531
It was your dream
to be a councilman, wasn't it?

656
00:37:17,131 --> 00:37:18,141
Hey.

657
00:37:18,871 --> 00:37:19,871
What?

658
00:37:20,501 --> 00:37:21,511
You don't...

659
00:37:22,111 --> 00:37:23,341
really mean that.

660
00:37:25,511 --> 00:37:26,511
Instead of saying that,

661
00:37:27,281 --> 00:37:29,151
you should talk it over
with your family.

662
00:37:29,781 --> 00:37:32,221
I'm going to talk with Se Ri, too.

663
00:37:37,051 --> 00:37:38,061
Hello.

664
00:37:38,391 --> 00:37:40,591
- Hello.
- Hello, Ma'am.

665
00:37:40,761 --> 00:37:44,191
I'm so sorry I'm late.
It's been so hectic at the store.

666
00:37:45,261 --> 00:37:47,031
So, what's going on?

667
00:37:47,831 --> 00:37:50,071
Congratulations.
Cha Se Ri, your store...

668
00:37:50,131 --> 00:37:52,371
was selected
as a top-performing location.

669
00:37:53,541 --> 00:37:57,311
- Oh, my, really?
- Yes. We appreciate how diligent...

670
00:37:57,371 --> 00:37:59,811
and meticulous you are
in running your store.

671
00:38:02,081 --> 00:38:05,081
I was just frantically trying
to follow the company manual,

672
00:38:05,781 --> 00:38:08,751
so I'm thrilled to actually
be getting an award for it.

673
00:38:09,821 --> 00:38:13,921
We've never seen anyone get selected
for this award so quickly.

674
00:38:14,791 --> 00:38:16,961
Make sure to dress up
for the awards ceremony.

675
00:38:17,431 --> 00:38:19,901
Oh, there's a ceremony?

676
00:38:20,861 --> 00:38:23,231
Wow, you finally got
the top-performing store award?

677
00:38:23,601 --> 00:38:27,671
That's my girl, right?
Not just anyone gets that.

678
00:38:27,811 --> 00:38:30,911
- This is all thanks to you.
- Oh, wait a minute.

679
00:38:31,411 --> 00:38:35,751
- Can I come to the awards ceremony?
- Honey, you're embarrassing me.

680
00:38:36,551 --> 00:38:39,221
Oh, right. You said you had
something to discuss with me?

681
00:38:39,221 --> 00:38:41,651
Well, about that...

682
00:38:42,921 --> 00:38:43,921
Honey,

683
00:38:44,591 --> 00:38:47,221
to get the nomination, I'll have to
do whatever it takes, right?

684
00:38:47,931 --> 00:38:49,931
Of course.
Becoming a city councilman...

685
00:38:49,991 --> 00:38:50,991
is your dream.

686
00:38:52,061 --> 00:38:53,261
That's true,

687
00:38:53,701 --> 00:38:56,601
but there's something
that's bothering me.

688
00:38:57,231 --> 00:38:59,141
What is it? What's the problem?

689
00:39:01,211 --> 00:39:03,171
Councilor Hwang told Dr. Yang...

690
00:39:03,241 --> 00:39:04,711
to get rid of Onjeong Market?

691
00:39:05,011 --> 00:39:06,981
That Councilor Hwang
is going too far.

692
00:39:07,311 --> 00:39:08,711
After making such a fuss...

693
00:39:08,781 --> 00:39:10,611
to win the market vendors' votes
during the election.

694
00:39:11,551 --> 00:39:12,781
To be honest,

695
00:39:13,351 --> 00:39:15,251
I don't think getting a landmark
in Onjeong...

696
00:39:15,321 --> 00:39:16,491
would be such a bad thing.

697
00:39:16,621 --> 00:39:20,591
That may be, but what about
the people at the market?

698
00:39:21,291 --> 00:39:22,891
Leave me out of this.

699
00:39:24,131 --> 00:39:25,131
You all talk among yourselves.

700
00:39:29,501 --> 00:39:31,571
The market is really
struggling these days.

701
00:39:31,941 --> 00:39:33,771
Fewer customers and fewer vendors.

702
00:39:34,641 --> 00:39:37,671
Frankly, a landmark might be better
for everyone involved.

703
00:39:38,581 --> 00:39:39,811
As the Merchants' Association
President,

704
00:39:39,881 --> 00:39:41,581
aren't you being incredibly
irresponsible?

705
00:39:42,051 --> 00:39:43,611
Why are you being like this?

706
00:39:44,311 --> 00:39:45,621
To be honest,

707
00:39:46,451 --> 00:39:49,291
I'm just disillusioned
with the market vendors.

708
00:39:52,861 --> 00:39:54,091
Do you feel that way too?

709
00:39:55,091 --> 00:39:58,161
Yes, I have mixed feelings
about it too.

710
00:39:58,501 --> 00:40:01,801
Maybe we were too naive
and just believed the rumors.

711
00:40:01,931 --> 00:40:05,671
We didn't believe in rumors.
We believed in people.

712
00:40:05,901 --> 00:40:08,071
Is it wrong to trust people?

713
00:40:08,071 --> 00:40:10,041
The ones who spread
malicious rumors are at fault.

714
00:40:20,881 --> 00:40:23,791
Did you change your mind
because of what happened with Jo Mi Hyang?

715
00:40:24,321 --> 00:40:26,621
I mean, even if everyone else
is against it,

716
00:40:26,821 --> 00:40:29,361
I thought you'd be for it.
This is surprising.

717
00:40:29,731 --> 00:40:31,831
You always hated it
when I got involved...

718
00:40:31,901 --> 00:40:33,761
with the market vendors' business.

719
00:40:33,961 --> 00:40:37,201
That was when
you ignored our family...

720
00:40:37,301 --> 00:40:39,401
and only cared about others.

721
00:40:40,741 --> 00:40:45,541
I married you because I loved
how kind and caring you were.

722
00:40:46,281 --> 00:40:47,741
Yes, I know.

723
00:40:48,411 --> 00:40:49,681
This isn't like you.

724
00:40:50,611 --> 00:40:53,621
If you turn your back on the market
like this, you'll regret it later.

725
00:40:54,751 --> 00:40:56,991
Okay, I'll think about it.

726
00:40:57,421 --> 00:40:59,621
Here, don't get stressed out
about this.

727
00:40:59,621 --> 00:41:01,891
I'm turning in for the night.

728
00:41:11,101 --> 00:41:12,371
- My gosh.
- There.

729
00:41:12,441 --> 00:41:14,371
- It stings.
- Let me hold it like this. There.

730
00:41:15,511 --> 00:41:16,911
How is it? Feeling better?

731
00:41:17,541 --> 00:41:19,311
Much better.

732
00:41:21,781 --> 00:41:24,151
What's wrong? Why?
Are you upset about something?

733
00:41:26,521 --> 00:41:30,521
I feel like my family doesn't take
my opinions seriously anymore.

734
00:41:30,751 --> 00:41:33,121
That can't be true.

735
00:41:33,491 --> 00:41:34,761
Of course not.

736
00:41:35,361 --> 00:41:37,091
But I feel so helpless
for some reason.

737
00:41:37,791 --> 00:41:40,861
I wonder if my words don't carry
any weight because I'm sick.

738
00:41:41,371 --> 00:41:45,041
What are you talking about?
Mom, you're Dr. Han Seong Mi.

739
00:41:45,701 --> 00:41:49,041
Honestly, I don't even know
if I can go back to broadcasting.

740
00:41:50,311 --> 00:41:51,541
You know better than anyone that...

741
00:41:51,611 --> 00:41:53,811
when you're physically worn out,
your spirit weakens too.

742
00:41:55,351 --> 00:41:56,411
You're right.

743
00:41:56,881 --> 00:41:59,251
- I need to get my head straight.
- Right.

744
00:41:59,321 --> 00:42:00,351
Let's talk about something else.

745
00:42:02,051 --> 00:42:05,821
The brand I launched did well
and was absorbed into Taehan Fashion.

746
00:42:06,321 --> 00:42:07,321
Taehan Fashion?

747
00:42:07,391 --> 00:42:12,031
Yes. And they asked me
to come back and work for them.

748
00:42:12,531 --> 00:42:14,131
Really? That's great.

749
00:42:15,331 --> 00:42:17,401
Then why the long face?

750
00:42:17,871 --> 00:42:21,071
I quit to avoid
running into Director Yang.

751
00:42:21,341 --> 00:42:22,741
But if I go back...

752
00:42:23,041 --> 00:42:26,011
Hey, you already worked together...

753
00:42:26,341 --> 00:42:28,111
as business partners.

754
00:42:28,711 --> 00:42:30,351
You two are in-laws.
Besides, you both said...

755
00:42:30,411 --> 00:42:32,551
you don't have romantic feelings
for each other, right?

756
00:42:33,151 --> 00:42:34,151
Right...

757
00:42:39,921 --> 00:42:40,921
Tell me.

758
00:42:42,061 --> 00:42:43,431
What did Mi Hyang say?

759
00:42:47,601 --> 00:42:48,601
Tell me.

760
00:42:50,371 --> 00:42:53,501
She said I lived my life
being deceived by what people said.

761
00:42:54,811 --> 00:42:58,211
She called me
a pathetic, naive fool.

762
00:42:59,941 --> 00:43:02,281
So you don't want to live
like that anymore?

763
00:43:03,581 --> 00:43:06,251
When kindness given
with a pure heart...

764
00:43:06,751 --> 00:43:08,451
comes back to you as poison...

765
00:43:10,991 --> 00:43:12,791
I'm scared of people now.

766
00:43:18,061 --> 00:43:19,061
Take my hand.

767
00:43:20,161 --> 00:43:23,671
- I'm fine.
- The path is rough.

768
00:43:24,001 --> 00:43:25,241
Take my hand.

769
00:43:25,841 --> 00:43:27,601
What if you fall?

770
00:43:28,811 --> 00:43:30,941
I've walked this path alone
for 30 years.

771
00:43:45,761 --> 00:43:47,561
Oh, Father.

772
00:43:49,531 --> 00:43:52,161
How do you find writing
in the memory journal?

773
00:43:53,631 --> 00:43:56,101
Well, writing down
fragments of memories...

774
00:43:56,171 --> 00:43:57,401
that come to mind...

775
00:43:57,731 --> 00:44:00,171
makes me feel like my head
is a little clearer.

776
00:44:01,771 --> 00:44:03,511
If you don't mind,

777
00:44:04,011 --> 00:44:07,041
would you like to share
what you wrote with me?

778
00:44:07,981 --> 00:44:12,121
You know,
you're not feeling well, are you?

779
00:44:13,951 --> 00:44:15,791
You noticed?

780
00:44:16,291 --> 00:44:20,061
Goodness, why do the women here
hide when they struggle?

781
00:44:20,361 --> 00:44:21,891
Oh, is that so?

782
00:44:22,261 --> 00:44:23,461
I'm telling you.

783
00:44:23,631 --> 00:44:26,301
You and your mother-in-law
are both the same,

784
00:44:26,501 --> 00:44:28,731
always acting so tough.

785
00:44:29,631 --> 00:44:30,631
I see.

786
00:44:31,231 --> 00:44:33,201
I wanted to be like Mother,
so I guess...

787
00:44:33,271 --> 00:44:35,441
I ended up being like her
in that way too.

788
00:44:36,711 --> 00:44:38,241
In your opinion,

789
00:44:39,181 --> 00:44:41,241
what kind of person is Na Seon Hae?

790
00:44:41,581 --> 00:44:42,581
Mother?

791
00:44:43,281 --> 00:44:46,381
My mother-in-law?
She's an incredible woman.

792
00:44:46,451 --> 00:44:47,451
For 30 years,

793
00:44:47,521 --> 00:44:49,151
she's had
the responsibility of protecting...

794
00:44:49,221 --> 00:44:50,691
the family, even doing your part,

795
00:44:51,121 --> 00:44:53,061
and she's endured
every single hardship...

796
00:44:53,121 --> 00:44:54,121
that came her way.

797
00:44:55,091 --> 00:44:56,091
Why, Father?

798
00:44:57,091 --> 00:44:58,091
No reason,

799
00:44:59,401 --> 00:45:02,271
I try to help her, but she refuses
to rely on me at all.

800
00:45:03,071 --> 00:45:06,171
It's because she's forgotten
how to rely on others.

801
00:45:06,901 --> 00:45:09,841
In your memory,
what kind of person am I?

802
00:45:13,041 --> 00:45:15,751
You were similar to Gong Jeong Han.

803
00:45:16,751 --> 00:45:17,951
So I was affectionate?

804
00:45:18,321 --> 00:45:22,621
Yes. You treated each
and every patient like family,

805
00:45:22,821 --> 00:45:25,721
you were good at telling jokes,
and you were a very warm person.

806
00:45:26,391 --> 00:45:28,061
You also took the lead
in the market's affairs.

807
00:45:31,731 --> 00:45:32,731
What is it?

808
00:45:33,101 --> 00:45:36,101
I created
the Merchants' Association.

809
00:45:36,531 --> 00:45:39,271
I asked Seon Chul to be
the Vice Chairman.

810
00:45:39,441 --> 00:45:41,141
Oh, my, you remember?

811
00:45:41,771 --> 00:45:42,771
A little.

812
00:45:44,371 --> 00:45:46,941
I think I'm starting to remember
what kind of person I am.

813
00:45:49,551 --> 00:45:51,721
I loved making people laugh.

814
00:45:52,551 --> 00:45:54,581
I liked seeing their smiling faces.

815
00:45:54,581 --> 00:45:56,621
This obstructing traffic charge...

816
00:45:56,691 --> 00:45:58,791
- Thank you.
- Oh, my goodness.

817
00:45:58,791 --> 00:46:01,061
Here, this way. A little more.

818
00:46:01,491 --> 00:46:03,691
I also liked to meddle in
other people's business.

819
00:46:04,531 --> 00:46:06,361
- Dr. Gong, hello.
- Oh, dear.

820
00:46:06,361 --> 00:46:08,031
I liked helping others too.

821
00:46:12,671 --> 00:46:16,011
Yes, I was someone
who really liked people.

822
00:46:16,571 --> 00:46:18,141
(Onjeong Traditional Market)

823
00:46:23,211 --> 00:46:24,851
Gosh, oh my.

824
00:46:24,921 --> 00:46:26,881
Oh, did you take
a trip to the market?

825
00:46:27,521 --> 00:46:28,921
Father, you used to do that
in the old days too.

826
00:46:30,991 --> 00:46:33,591
That's right.
I used to go out there...

827
00:46:33,621 --> 00:46:35,861
and wander around all the time.

828
00:46:38,501 --> 00:46:39,501
Yes.

829
00:46:40,401 --> 00:46:45,201
- Some of my memories are back.
- Oh, really, Father?

830
00:46:45,271 --> 00:46:48,741
Father. What do you remember?

831
00:46:50,641 --> 00:46:52,541
Come on, please tell us.

832
00:46:52,941 --> 00:46:53,941
I went...

833
00:46:55,351 --> 00:46:56,851
because I wanted to.

834
00:46:58,181 --> 00:47:00,851
The house call to Jo Mun Sik
30 years ago.

835
00:47:02,051 --> 00:47:03,421
Jeong Han told me not to go,

836
00:47:03,491 --> 00:47:05,521
asking where I was going
so late at night,

837
00:47:05,591 --> 00:47:06,961
but I insisted.

838
00:47:07,691 --> 00:47:11,031
"Since no one else is coming,
shouldn't I be the one to go?"

839
00:47:11,631 --> 00:47:13,601
Yes, well, that's what you did.

840
00:47:14,431 --> 00:47:15,471
But you know what?

841
00:47:16,001 --> 00:47:17,631
Even if I could turn back time,

842
00:47:19,601 --> 00:47:21,071
I think I'd go again.

843
00:47:21,471 --> 00:47:22,971
Because that's
the kind of person I am.

844
00:47:23,471 --> 00:47:24,471
Yes.

845
00:47:24,811 --> 00:47:26,411
That's the kind of person
you were, Father.

846
00:47:27,181 --> 00:47:28,181
Jeong Han.

847
00:47:29,481 --> 00:47:31,151
Your patients bring you
tasty food...

848
00:47:31,211 --> 00:47:33,551
and praise you
for being a compassionate doctor.

849
00:47:33,621 --> 00:47:35,421
Do you treat them
because you like that?

850
00:47:35,791 --> 00:47:37,891
Oh, of course not.

851
00:47:38,151 --> 00:47:40,921
- I do it because I love it.
- Exactly.

852
00:47:41,191 --> 00:47:43,961
You do it because you want to.
That's who you are.

853
00:47:45,301 --> 00:47:48,731
- Yes.
- Not because I'm a good person,

854
00:47:49,131 --> 00:47:51,371
or because you're a kind person.

855
00:47:51,771 --> 00:47:54,571
We make these choices
simply because we want to.

856
00:47:55,141 --> 00:47:56,441
That's my point, Father.

857
00:47:56,511 --> 00:47:58,911
Let's not live like that anymore.
Okay?

858
00:47:59,411 --> 00:48:00,411
He's right, Father.

859
00:48:00,741 --> 00:48:02,981
Living like that is why
we lost 30 years of our lives.

860
00:48:04,211 --> 00:48:05,221
But I don't want to change.

861
00:48:06,381 --> 00:48:08,551
Listen. I don't think anything is...

862
00:48:08,621 --> 00:48:11,921
- wrong with the way I lived.
- Oh, Father.

863
00:48:12,291 --> 00:48:14,461
I'm not saying we have to be saints.

864
00:48:14,961 --> 00:48:16,991
And I'm not saying
we should forgive anyone.

865
00:48:17,791 --> 00:48:21,131
I'm still resentful. And angry.
When I think about it,

866
00:48:21,201 --> 00:48:23,001
my heart feels like
it's going to burst.

867
00:48:24,271 --> 00:48:26,571
But our brilliant daughter-in-law
said it herself.

868
00:48:26,901 --> 00:48:31,071
We didn't believe in rumors.
We believed in people.

869
00:48:31,371 --> 00:48:34,341
But if we start hating people now
and get rid of the market,

870
00:48:35,081 --> 00:48:38,311
it won't be Jo Mi Hyang
who took 30 years from us.

871
00:48:38,681 --> 00:48:41,251
We will have lost who we are.

872
00:48:41,691 --> 00:48:42,751
Wait, Father.

873
00:48:43,091 --> 00:48:45,691
Is this all because we're trying
to get rid of the market?

874
00:48:46,161 --> 00:48:47,161
Yes.

875
00:48:48,221 --> 00:48:49,631
Don't do it, Jeong Han.

876
00:48:51,131 --> 00:48:52,461
Let's save the market.

877
00:48:53,561 --> 00:48:57,531
Hey. I'm the one who created
the Merchants' Association.

878
00:48:58,841 --> 00:49:00,471
I want to save the market.

879
00:49:03,841 --> 00:49:05,911
Come on, let's eat.
The food's getting cold.

880
00:49:06,281 --> 00:49:07,941
Hey, this is still delicious.
It's even good cold.

881
00:49:17,821 --> 00:49:21,091
Hey, are you really sure about this?

882
00:49:21,361 --> 00:49:25,101
- You got your wife's permission?
- Yes.

883
00:49:25,431 --> 00:49:26,601
She said she'd go along
with my decision.

884
00:49:27,901 --> 00:49:30,631
She said she'll respect my choices
from now on.

885
00:49:32,201 --> 00:49:34,701
Well, that's a relief. Right?

886
00:49:37,971 --> 00:49:38,981
Oh, there he is.

887
00:49:39,881 --> 00:49:41,441
Oh, you're here?

888
00:49:41,881 --> 00:49:43,211
Dr. Gong, you're here as well?

889
00:49:43,551 --> 00:49:44,551
Yes.

890
00:49:47,251 --> 00:49:49,121
Don't tell me
you came to convince me...

891
00:49:49,191 --> 00:49:50,351
to change my platform.

892
00:49:51,121 --> 00:49:52,121
Councilor Hwang.

893
00:49:52,961 --> 00:49:54,491
About Onjeong Market...

894
00:49:55,261 --> 00:49:56,631
Do you really have to tear it down?

895
00:49:57,131 --> 00:50:00,131
I hate repeating myself.

896
00:50:05,641 --> 00:50:09,571
Then I can't be on your side,
Councilor Hwang.

897
00:50:10,241 --> 00:50:11,541
I'm giving up the nomination.

898
00:50:12,181 --> 00:50:14,811
Are you saying you're not running
for city council?

899
00:50:14,881 --> 00:50:17,781
Oh, no. I still have to run.

900
00:50:23,951 --> 00:50:26,091
So, as an independent?

901
00:50:26,521 --> 00:50:28,691
No. Not as an independent.

902
00:50:30,031 --> 00:50:32,861
- Then under what party?
- I, Yang Dong Ik,

903
00:50:34,331 --> 00:50:35,871
belong to Onjeong Market.

904
00:50:39,301 --> 00:50:40,301
Right.

905
00:50:43,471 --> 00:50:44,471
We've got this.

906
00:50:48,441 --> 00:50:50,411
You don't like my decision?

907
00:50:53,081 --> 00:50:55,291
I know you're right,

908
00:50:56,151 --> 00:50:57,621
but it's just so hard for me
to accept.

909
00:50:58,491 --> 00:51:01,521
Well, if it's hard,
if you don't like it,

910
00:51:01,961 --> 00:51:04,891
just say so. I'll listen to
whatever you have to say.

911
00:51:06,631 --> 00:51:09,701
- It's okay.
- What do you mean, it's okay?

912
00:51:10,531 --> 00:51:13,241
If you want to cry, then cry.
If you're angry, get angry.

913
00:51:13,301 --> 00:51:15,311
If you're upset, then be upset.

914
00:51:16,311 --> 00:51:18,781
Stop holding it all in.

915
00:51:20,581 --> 00:51:21,681
Na Seon Hae...

916
00:51:22,181 --> 00:51:24,181
was never one
to pretend to be strong...

917
00:51:24,251 --> 00:51:25,521
and tough it out alone.

918
00:51:26,151 --> 00:51:29,221
Whenever she had a hard time,
she would always come to me first.

919
00:51:29,291 --> 00:51:32,891
She was someone who relied on me.
She laughed a lot and cried a lot.

920
00:51:33,391 --> 00:51:35,961
She could never hide
what was on her mind.

921
00:51:38,361 --> 00:51:39,361
You...

922
00:51:40,401 --> 00:51:41,871
Have your memories returned?

923
00:51:43,401 --> 00:51:45,131
Want to see if my memories are back?

924
00:51:52,081 --> 00:51:53,581
Woo Jae taught me.

925
00:51:58,451 --> 00:52:00,781
("Hold My Hand")

926
00:52:11,191 --> 00:52:12,201
Hold it.

927
00:52:14,401 --> 00:52:15,401
Honey.

928
00:52:15,871 --> 00:52:17,931
That's right. I'm your husband.

929
00:52:18,401 --> 00:52:20,901
So it's okay for you
to hold my hand.

930
00:53:03,811 --> 00:53:06,021
You've been holding on
by yourself for so long,

931
00:53:07,551 --> 00:53:09,221
have you forgotten
how to lean on someone?

932
00:53:11,051 --> 00:53:12,061
It's okay to cry.

933
00:53:13,121 --> 00:53:14,891
You can lean on me and cry.

934
00:53:15,691 --> 00:53:16,991
I'm not going anywhere now.

935
00:53:17,791 --> 00:53:19,401
Your husband is right here.

936
00:53:51,631 --> 00:53:54,431
(Taehan)

937
00:53:56,601 --> 00:53:59,041
We finally made it to Taehan.

938
00:53:59,941 --> 00:54:01,741
- This is awesome.
- We're finally here.

939
00:54:02,011 --> 00:54:03,311
This place is the best.

940
00:54:07,281 --> 00:54:08,281
Is everyone here?

941
00:54:08,881 --> 00:54:10,951
- There he is!
- There he is!

942
00:54:12,081 --> 00:54:13,081
Hold on a second.

943
00:54:13,681 --> 00:54:15,181
We can't just gloss over this.

944
00:54:15,251 --> 00:54:17,121
Not after
what you all put me through.

945
00:54:17,321 --> 00:54:20,361
Well, you should have told us.

946
00:54:20,421 --> 00:54:23,631
Hey, I told them not to.
We needed it to be top secret.

947
00:54:24,061 --> 00:54:28,701
Seriously, I was so stressed out.
You all owe me an apology.

948
00:54:28,771 --> 00:54:31,031
We're sorry. For our sake,

949
00:54:31,101 --> 00:54:32,501
we didn't even realize
how hard you were working.

950
00:54:32,841 --> 00:54:34,171
- We're sorry.
- We're sorry.

951
00:54:34,901 --> 00:54:37,041
Okay, I'll be cool and forgive you.

952
00:54:37,641 --> 00:54:40,311
So, does this mean
you're returning to the Design Team?

953
00:54:40,681 --> 00:54:44,081
Of course. I'm the designer,
Hwangbo Jun Hyeok.

954
00:54:44,481 --> 00:54:47,051
- Yes!
- I'm so touched.

955
00:54:47,081 --> 00:54:49,721
But what's going to happen
to CEO Gong?

956
00:54:49,991 --> 00:54:53,761
I know. I requested his return,
but I'm not sure what will happen.

957
00:54:55,291 --> 00:54:56,831
What do you think will happen?

958
00:54:57,491 --> 00:54:59,931
Do you think I'd just give away
our precious Pelliv for nothing?

959
00:55:00,061 --> 00:55:01,401
- Ms. Gong.
- Ms. Gong.

960
00:55:01,931 --> 00:55:05,401
Gong Ju Ah reporting for duty
at Taehan, Director Yang.

961
00:55:07,541 --> 00:55:10,471
It's good to see you.
Welcome back, Ms. Gong.

962
00:55:24,051 --> 00:55:26,191
(Hanguk University Hospital)

963
00:55:29,031 --> 00:55:30,791
Yes, this is Yang Seon Chul.

964
00:55:31,261 --> 00:55:33,031
Yes, this is
Hanguk University Hospital.

965
00:55:33,761 --> 00:55:35,101
Are the test results back?

966
00:55:35,431 --> 00:55:39,071
Yes, sir. We're calling because
your condition is quite urgent.

967
00:55:39,701 --> 00:55:42,771
What on earth is my diagnosis?

968
00:55:43,371 --> 00:55:45,641
It's Acute Myeloid Leukemia.

969
00:55:46,641 --> 00:55:48,811
You need to come in
as soon as possible...

970
00:55:48,881 --> 00:55:50,111
to start chemotherapy.

971
00:55:58,861 --> 00:56:02,891
(3H Acupressure Bed,
Outstanding Store, First Half of 2026)

972
00:56:02,961 --> 00:56:04,331
Store Owner Cha Se Ri.

973
00:56:05,291 --> 00:56:06,801
For the first half of 2026,

974
00:56:07,401 --> 00:56:09,501
congratulations on being selected
as the top-performing store.

975
00:56:10,101 --> 00:56:12,031
Because you have illuminated
the value of our brand...

976
00:56:12,101 --> 00:56:13,241
with your exceptional passion,

977
00:56:13,301 --> 00:56:17,771
we present this award
with our gratitude and respect.

978
00:56:18,881 --> 00:56:19,941
Thank you.

979
00:56:20,011 --> 00:56:22,811
(Certified Medical Device Bed,
Heat, Acupressure, Massage)

980
00:56:22,911 --> 00:56:25,081
Going forward,
with the head office's PR team,

981
00:56:25,351 --> 00:56:27,651
if you would share
your unique methods...

982
00:56:27,721 --> 00:56:30,721
with the other store owners,
we would be very grateful.

983
00:56:31,921 --> 00:56:34,421
Manager Cha.
Would you like to say a few words?

984
00:56:34,991 --> 00:56:35,991
Yes.

985
00:56:36,061 --> 00:56:37,961
(Selected As Outstanding Store
For 3H Acupressure Bed, Half 2026)

986
00:56:38,491 --> 00:56:40,401
Hello, I'm Cha Se Ri.

987
00:56:41,801 --> 00:56:44,231
Instead of just demonstrating
the product,

988
00:56:44,301 --> 00:56:46,501
I let customers
experience it directly...

989
00:56:46,571 --> 00:56:50,471
to show its excellence,
which I believe led to this award.

990
00:56:50,941 --> 00:56:51,971
In the future,
I will continue to work...

991
00:56:52,041 --> 00:56:53,041
with the head office's PR team...

992
00:56:53,111 --> 00:56:55,981
to help even more people
experience our products,

993
00:56:56,211 --> 00:56:59,521
always prioritizing our customers'
healthy daily lives.

994
00:56:59,781 --> 00:57:02,921
That's how I'll become
Store Owner Cha. Thank you.

995
00:57:04,321 --> 00:57:06,621
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

996
00:57:06,821 --> 00:57:08,861
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

997
00:57:09,561 --> 00:57:10,631
If you memorize the short sentences,

998
00:57:10,731 --> 00:57:12,131
it becomes easier
to comprehend the long ones.

999
00:57:12,361 --> 00:57:13,461
Just memorize them all.

1000
00:57:13,931 --> 00:57:16,371
And you have a vocabulary test
next week.

1001
00:57:16,971 --> 00:57:17,971
Gosh, come on.

1002
00:57:19,141 --> 00:57:20,901
What do you mean, "gosh, come on?"

1003
00:57:23,911 --> 00:57:25,411
By the way,

1004
00:57:25,681 --> 00:57:27,341
is your sister busy these days?

1005
00:57:27,711 --> 00:57:28,711
Yes.

1006
00:57:29,211 --> 00:57:30,211
Why?

1007
00:57:30,581 --> 00:57:33,221
What do you mean, "why?"
I was just asking.

1008
00:57:34,351 --> 00:57:35,381
I don't think so.

1009
00:57:36,021 --> 00:57:37,021
What do you mean?

1010
00:57:37,091 --> 00:57:38,961
You're talking back more and more
these days.

1011
00:57:42,691 --> 00:57:45,831
Hey, in-law.

1012
00:57:46,101 --> 00:57:47,501
Eun Bin.

1013
00:57:48,601 --> 00:57:51,901
Hey, we finally meet.
My schedule ended early today,

1014
00:57:51,971 --> 00:57:53,401
so I was just about to call you.

1015
00:57:54,271 --> 00:57:57,711
- Why?
- Because I told you I'd treat you.

1016
00:57:58,611 --> 00:58:01,411
Oh, right. I forgot.

1017
00:58:02,181 --> 00:58:04,781
So, are you free now?
I'm getting hungry.

1018
00:58:05,781 --> 00:58:07,151
Do you have to go to your
part-time job?

1019
00:58:07,451 --> 00:58:09,391
No, it's actually my day off today.

1020
00:58:09,851 --> 00:58:10,851
Really?

1021
00:58:20,531 --> 00:58:22,601
- Excuse me.
- Hello.

1022
00:58:23,701 --> 00:58:26,341
By any chance, is Hyun Bin here?

1023
00:58:27,671 --> 00:58:29,071
We're having a company dinner today.

1024
00:58:30,341 --> 00:58:31,771
He went to his aunt's restaurant.

1025
00:58:32,171 --> 00:58:33,381
Really?

1026
00:58:33,941 --> 00:58:35,881
My goodness.

1027
00:58:35,951 --> 00:58:38,581
Oh my, this company must hire people
based on their looks.

1028
00:58:38,751 --> 00:58:40,121
Why is everyone so handsome?

1029
00:58:42,321 --> 00:58:45,451
We have a new menu item.
Would you like to try it?

1030
00:58:46,261 --> 00:58:47,361
It looks delicious.

1031
00:58:47,921 --> 00:58:48,921
We'll go with that.

1032
00:58:48,991 --> 00:58:51,461
And please bring us enough
to cover the entire table.

1033
00:58:51,631 --> 00:58:54,631
- Yes.
- He sure is on another level.

1034
00:58:54,931 --> 00:58:56,031
Jun Hyeok,
you're quite the big spender.

1035
00:58:56,101 --> 00:58:58,371
So you want us to cover the table
with everything from here to here?

1036
00:58:58,831 --> 00:59:02,071
- Yes.
- All with meat? Okay.

1037
00:59:02,141 --> 00:59:03,411
- One moment.
- Thank you.

1038
00:59:03,471 --> 00:59:05,541
- Excuse me.
- Everyone, let's make a toast.

1039
00:59:05,611 --> 00:59:08,511
- Here.
- To all our hard work.

1040
00:59:16,191 --> 00:59:18,491
The meat is so tender,
it melts in your mouth.

1041
00:59:18,551 --> 00:59:20,791
I know, right?
It's a flavor anyone would love.

1042
00:59:21,791 --> 00:59:25,191
All right, I ordered more meat,
so everyone, eat up.

1043
00:59:25,361 --> 00:59:26,861
Okay, thank you.

1044
00:59:28,201 --> 00:59:29,971
I think this is all cooked.

1045
00:59:32,001 --> 00:59:34,141
It's not cooked yet.

1046
00:59:36,871 --> 00:59:38,541
This is all cooked.

1047
00:59:39,281 --> 00:59:41,381
I like my meat well-done.

1048
00:59:42,511 --> 00:59:44,151
That stubbornness.

1049
00:59:44,781 --> 00:59:46,851
Hey, who are you calling pigheaded?

1050
00:59:47,251 --> 00:59:49,851
Gosh, can't you two
just get back together?

1051
00:59:50,321 --> 00:59:53,621
- Oh my.
- Be quiet, we're in-laws.

1052
00:59:53,761 --> 00:59:56,091
Hey, what's the big deal about being
double In-laws these days?

1053
00:59:56,161 --> 00:59:59,301
- Forget it.
- I don't want to either.

1054
00:59:59,631 --> 01:00:02,831
All right.
Should we make a bet then?

1055
01:00:03,271 --> 01:00:05,301
On whether or not
they get back together.

1056
01:00:06,041 --> 01:00:08,441
- I vote they get back together.
- Together.

1057
01:00:08,501 --> 01:00:09,971
- Together.
- I vote they get back together too.

1058
01:00:10,041 --> 01:00:11,341
- Together.
- Together.

1059
01:00:11,411 --> 01:00:12,641
- Together.
- Together.

1060
01:00:12,711 --> 01:00:13,711
Together.

1061
01:00:14,011 --> 01:00:15,381
- Together.
- Together.

1062
01:00:15,611 --> 01:00:16,981
- Together.
- Together.

1063
01:00:17,151 --> 01:00:19,251
- Together.
- You all must be crazy.

1064
01:00:19,521 --> 01:00:20,651
What are you all doing?

1065
01:00:22,321 --> 01:00:24,051
Keep eating.
I'm stepping out for a bit.

1066
01:00:28,691 --> 01:00:29,691
Hey.

1067
01:00:31,391 --> 01:00:33,901
Just make a toast. Cheers.

1068
01:00:35,261 --> 01:00:37,271
(Noodle Soup)

1069
01:00:44,641 --> 01:00:45,741
Cheers.

1070
01:00:47,311 --> 01:00:48,311
What are you doing?

1071
01:00:48,411 --> 01:00:50,911
I had a feeling I'd find you
out here all by yourself.

1072
01:00:51,581 --> 01:00:52,581
So?

1073
01:00:52,881 --> 01:00:55,251
What does it matter to you
if I'm alone or not?

1074
01:00:56,621 --> 01:00:57,791
I came because I was worried.

1075
01:00:59,051 --> 01:01:01,621
Don't worry about me.
There's nothing between us.

1076
01:01:14,101 --> 01:01:16,411
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

1077
01:01:18,171 --> 01:01:20,141
Oh, hello.

1078
01:01:20,641 --> 01:01:21,681
Oh, Vice President.

1079
01:01:21,741 --> 01:01:24,281
Why are you just standing here?
Aren't you going in?

1080
01:01:25,921 --> 01:01:28,821
Well... By any chance...

1081
01:01:29,151 --> 01:01:32,351
Could you please get Hyun Bin
for me if he's inside?

1082
01:01:32,961 --> 01:01:33,961
Sure.

1083
01:01:34,621 --> 01:01:35,621
Excuse me.

1084
01:01:36,791 --> 01:01:37,791
Yes?

1085
01:01:38,091 --> 01:01:40,301
I'm just saying to set him up
with any woman.

1086
01:01:40,701 --> 01:01:43,571
Have I asked you for that much?
How can you say you can't do it?

1087
01:01:44,531 --> 01:01:46,101
By any chance...

1088
01:01:47,471 --> 01:01:49,641
- Interested in marrying Hyun Bin?
- Excuse me?

1089
01:01:49,711 --> 01:01:50,711
Now that I think about it,

1090
01:01:50,771 --> 01:01:53,711
it seems to me that you have
feelings for our Hyun Bin,

1091
01:01:53,781 --> 01:01:55,881
and Hyun Bin will be staying here
in Korea from now on.

1092
01:01:55,951 --> 01:01:56,981
Mother!

1093
01:02:02,851 --> 01:02:05,451
- Hyun Bin.
- What do you think you're doing?

1094
01:02:07,091 --> 01:02:08,761
Hyun Bin, it's just that...

1095
01:02:11,691 --> 01:02:13,961
I had no choice.
It was because of Grandfather.

1096
01:02:15,501 --> 01:02:17,831
I'm so sorry.
I know I was completely out of line.

1097
01:02:17,971 --> 01:02:20,341
- Whatever.
- Gosh...

1098
01:02:22,001 --> 01:02:23,371
I'm going to go in first.

1099
01:02:28,081 --> 01:02:30,751
Well, I should get going.

1100
01:02:32,151 --> 01:02:35,681
Wait. I'm sorry. Are you upset?

1101
01:02:37,591 --> 01:02:39,191
Why would I be upset?

1102
01:02:40,091 --> 01:02:41,461
Actually, you should go for it.

1103
01:02:41,991 --> 01:02:45,291
- Go for what?
- Marrying the Vice President...

1104
01:02:45,731 --> 01:02:48,331
- might not be such a bad idea.
- No, that's not...

1105
01:02:48,861 --> 01:02:51,201
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

1106
01:03:00,281 --> 01:03:01,281
Gong Ju Ah.

1107
01:03:02,581 --> 01:03:03,581
Ju Ah.

1108
01:03:06,251 --> 01:03:07,251
What?

1109
01:03:07,651 --> 01:03:08,751
Are you serious?

1110
01:03:09,051 --> 01:03:11,721
Do you really want me
to marry someone else?

1111
01:03:12,121 --> 01:03:13,591
Yes, I'm serious.

1112
01:03:14,091 --> 01:03:17,791
- You really mean it?
- Yes, I wish you would just do it.

1113
01:03:18,991 --> 01:03:20,001
That way,

1114
01:03:20,561 --> 01:03:22,631
I think I can finally get over you.

1115
01:03:28,041 --> 01:03:31,641
Don't look at me like that.
This is really hard for me.

1116
01:03:33,141 --> 01:03:34,881
If it's going to be hard either way,

1117
01:03:35,681 --> 01:03:38,311
then let's just struggle
through it together.

1118
01:03:40,421 --> 01:03:44,521
- What?
- If you say yes, I'll take it on.

1119
01:03:48,761 --> 01:03:49,831
I can't.

1120
01:03:50,391 --> 01:03:51,731
I'm not confident enough.

1121
01:03:53,261 --> 01:03:54,261
So you really...

1122
01:03:55,001 --> 01:03:56,071
can't do it?

1123
01:04:06,011 --> 01:04:07,311
I'm going to walk away.

1124
01:04:10,651 --> 01:04:11,951
Listen carefully, Gong Ju Ah.

1125
01:04:12,511 --> 01:04:13,921
If you let me go now,

1126
01:04:16,291 --> 01:04:17,521
we're really over.

1127
01:04:43,581 --> 01:04:44,611
Don't go.

1128
01:04:45,551 --> 01:04:46,951
Don't go, Yang Hyun Bin.

1129
01:04:48,421 --> 01:04:50,451
Don't turn your back on me.

1130
01:05:48,011 --> 01:05:50,781
(Recipe for Love)

1131
01:05:50,951 --> 01:05:54,781
The poll results from
Councilor Hwang's campaign are in.

1132
01:05:54,851 --> 01:05:58,391
Is that so?
How much did our Dong Ik get?

1133
01:05:59,621 --> 01:06:01,591
Only three percent.

1134
01:06:02,261 --> 01:06:04,161
I, Yang Hyun Bin,
want to spend the rest...

1135
01:06:04,231 --> 01:06:05,491
of my life with Gong Ju Ah.

1136
01:06:05,561 --> 01:06:07,501
Please give us
your blessing to marry.

1137
01:06:09,431 --> 01:06:11,631
Acute Myeloid Leukemia?

1138
01:06:11,701 --> 01:06:14,171
So you didn't tell anyone
and went through it alone...

1139
01:06:14,441 --> 01:06:16,471
That's why he was
in such a hurry for my wedding.

1140
01:06:16,641 --> 01:06:19,111
- Thanks, Gi Cheol's granddaughter.
- Of course.

1141
01:06:19,111 --> 01:06:20,311
Make a decision.

1142
01:06:22,171 --> 01:06:24,171
Dramaday.me
